President Trump announced new guidelines for Americans to follow over the next 15 days to combat the coronavirus. The White House Coronavirus Task Force is coordinating a nationwide response, and states are being given responsibility for authorizing tests developed and used by laboratories in their states. Medicare telehealth services will be expanded, allowing patients to visit doctors through phone or videoconference at no additional cost. The President is also working with the private sector to ensure the supply chains meet the demands of healthcare providers and the American people. Additionally, efforts are being made to provide economic relief to workers and industries affected by the pandemic. President Trump emphasized that the world is at war with a hidden enemy and expressed confidence in victory.